RACE.RACE_TEXT: REMINGTON PARK RACE 1 5 1/2F Dirt CR: 56. Maiden Claiming Purse 13000. FOR MAIDENS, FILLIES AND MARES THREE, FOUR, AND FIVE YEARS OLD. Three Year Olds, 118 lbs.; Older, 122 lbs. Claiming Price $10,000.
RACE.FOOTNOTES: SAN MATEO KAT was reserved off the early pace, rallied two-wide into the stretch splitting rivals, took the lead nearing the eighth pole and quickly drew clear. DAPHNE'S FIRE vied for the lead while racing three-wide, gained a slight lead nearing the quarter pole, was carried out five-wide entering the stretch when MAGICAL GOLD drifted out, then was unable to stay with the winner during the drive but finished well for second. ELENA MAE broke out and bumped YANKEES MIRACLES, then was allowed to settle while racing four-wide on the turn, came six-wide into the stretch and finished in a mild rally. TALKATIVE was unhurried early, rallied six-wide into the stretch, angled in during the drive and gained his best stride too late. MAGICAL GOLD saved ground setting the early pace, drifted out three-wide leaving the quarter pole and tired. IZEADISTORTEDLADY prompted the early pace while two-wide, angled to the inside when MAGICAL GOLD drifted out to offer a bid entering the stretch and then faltered during the drive. YANKEES MIRACLES was bumped at the start then settled in the middle of the field while racing two-wide but lacked a rally. LIGHTNING MELODY was off a step slow then saved ground and failed to seriously threaten. MUCH ALOHA was bumped at the start by DIAMONDS R FOREVER, then raced four-wide and failed to menace. DIAMONDS R FOREVER broke out sharply to bump MUCH ALOHA, then settled in the middle of the field while five-wide and gave way during the drive. FRECKLES broke in the air to get away behind his field, dropped far back and was distanced in the stretch, then walked off following the race.

RACE.RACE_TEXT: REMINGTON PARK RACE 2 1M Dirt CR: 91. Claiming Purse 12000. FOR THREE YEAR OLDS AND UPWARD. Three Year Olds, 117 lbs.; Older, 121 lbs. Claiming Price $5,000.
RACE.FOOTNOTES: TOMA TODO set the pace racing in hand while two-wide, opened clear nearing the stretch and drew off to win as much the best despite drifting out in the stretch. COLOR FAST was reserved off the pace while racing three-wide, came four-wide into the stretch and was up for second in a steady effort. JACKS SPRING BREAK vied for the early lead from along the inside, angled out to come three-wide into the stretch and held on well for third. HIT ONE OUT chased the pace while racing two-wide but lacked a rally. BIG POWER RED saved ground while being allowed to settle but lacked a response when called on. RIVER KAT was prominent for a half mile while racing three-wide and then gave way.

ENTRY.NAME: Toma Todo
ENTRY.COMMENT: set pace in hand, drifted out drive, much the best

RACE.FOOTNOTES: JOHNNY APPLESEED was reserved off the pace while racing five-wide on the turn, continued to be wide into the stretch, took the lead at the eighth pole, dueled with WISHERT from that point and proved best under strong handling. WISHERT was prominent while racing three-wide, moved up to join the leaders nearing the eighth pole, disputed the issue from that point and finished second in a game effort. TRUCKIN saved ground setting the pace, responded when headed and held on well for third/. SUPER PROSPECTOR saved ground while being unhurried, angled out to be three-wide during the drive and went evenly late. LONG COOL saved ground chasing the pace but lacked a rally. DOC'S BOLERO opened a clear lead shortly after that start then was taken back to stalk the pace while two-wide, drifted out to come six-wide into the stretch and tired.

RACE.FOOTNOTES: GYPSAN saved ground while being reserved off the early pace, slipped through entering the stretch, took the lead nearing the eighth pole and quickly drew clear. BOSS ON THE RUN vied with OVER BLINGED for the lead from along the inside, drifted out three-wide nearing the stretch and held on fairly well for second. CHAINSAW CITY was reserved off the pace while two-wide on the turn, came five-wide into the stretch and lacked a rally. FEND OFF hopped in the air at the start then saved ground and failed to menace. OVER BLINGED vied for the early lead from along the outside, dropped back slightly nearing the stretch, then ducked out approaching the eighth pole and tired.

STORMY CUT vied for the lead from along the inside for three furlongs, stopped and was eased up during the drive.
